        <title>Managing CentOS with SUSE Manager</title>
        <para>The following sections will guide you through preparing and adding centOS clients to
            SUSE Manager.start</para>

        <sect2>
            <title>Creating Channels and Repositories</title>
            <para>First you will need to create the required channels and repositories for
                centOS.</para>
            <procedure>
                <title>Adding the Base repository</title>
                <step>
                    <para>Login to your SUSE Manager WebUI and browse to:
                            <guimenu>Channels</guimenu> &gt; <guimenu>Manage Software
                            Channels</guimenu> &gt; <guimenu>Mange Repositories</guimenu> and select
                            <guimenu>Create New Repository</guimenu></para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Add Base repository details:</para>
                    <screen>Repository label: CentOS 6 Base x86_64
Repository URL: http://mirrors.kernel.org/centos/6/os/x86_64/

Has signed metadata? UNCHECKED</screen>
                </step>
                <step><para></para></step>
